        <title>ACTIVITY: Compare sizes [LO 4.2, LO 3.8]</title>
        <para id="id1166178744257">3. LET US COMPARE SIZES!</para>
        <para id="id1166168607714">The following rectangle has been enlarged first two times, then three times and then five times.</para>
        <figure id="id1166181026341">
          <media id="id1166181026341_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics1-07fb.png" id="id1166181026341__onlineimage" height="197" width="295"/>
          </media>
        </figure>
        <para id="id6282065">All the rectangles have the same ratio for length to breadth: 3:2.</para>
        <para id="id1166173770695">a) Look again at the rectangles above. Suppose that each block is 1 cm by 1 cm. Complete the table.</para>
        <table id="id1166174592529" summary="">
          <tgroup cols="5">
            <colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
            <colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
